":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"70ff5118d6237f9001f14f41792c8d587c6ca80fcd6ca9484bcb9aa5bcae567e","event_uuid":"98ae9a8a-3076-496b-902f-4ff9adef92ee","position":{"commit_sha":"e3172920873b61bfc412d32aa5423208bfd7ef6a","position":"1784250110792344001-98ae9a8a-3076-496b-902f-4ff9adef92ee"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"8dfd6ed53fc2c713a67ddd62d26a51aef11d31ed5d8da105a9c5a2133649ed57","event_uuid":"956eb610-7702-417b-bee2-4feeac0f1290","position":{"commit_sha":"888474deeba697a30d83f935aef52053b035866b","position":"1784250112924045001-956eb610-7702-417b-bee2-4feeac0f1290"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-211_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"e533bbc2-be02-4c77-890b-73fde9abf109","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Fix pushed as Gerrit change 746 (https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/746), stacked atop 741. RE-ASSESSMENT (fixed build, signing live): ALL authored event types now sign through the shared finalize_event seam — CREATE, COMMENT, EDIT, FILE_IMPACT, STATUS(transition/claim/close), claim EDIT all show author_sig; 'rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated' exits 0 (every enforced event verifies). Held-out oracle 5/5 + teeth (mutating out finalize_event -> transition/close tests go RED). ruff+mypy clean. Full suite: 6217 passed / 3 failed — the 3 failures are config-show/perf tests that detect this machine's ~/.config/rebar/config.toml (from 79da) via a test-isolation gap; they PASS with that file absent and on CI (fresh runner). NOT a regression from this change. Follow-up ticket filed for the isolation gap.","timestamp":1784249110548224001}],"created_at":1784244231026683001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"6cd0b7fa-d1a4-4ca4-948e-f2e090755618","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"dc09-6565-cf85-4aea"}],"description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Configure local signing (`[identity] signing_key` set; git email resolves to an identity — e.g. 594c).\n2. `rebar create task \"t\"` -> the CREATE event is SIGNED (`author_sig` present).\n3. `rebar transition <t> open idea` (or any claim/transition/close) -> the STATUS event is written with `author_id` stamped but **NO `author_sig`** (UNSIGNED).\n4. `rebar verify-identity --all --format json` lists that STATUS event as `unsigned` (in-scope, enforceable).\n\n**Expected:** transition/claim/close STATUS (and claim EDIT) events sign like CREATE/COMMENT do.\n**Actual:** they are attributed but unsigned.\n\n## Root cause\n\nCREATE/COMMENT are written via `src/rebar/_commands/_seam.append_event`, which calls\n`_apply_authorship` (the signing seam + write-gate). But transitions/claims/closes are written\nvia `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py` (`transition_core` ~L249-268, `claim_core` ~L341-372): these\nbuild the STATUS/EDIT event dicts, merge `attribution` (author_email/author_id) but write them\ndirectly via `fsutil.atomic_write` + git commit, **never calling `_apply_authorship`**. So the\ntransactional path signs nothing AND bypasses the require_authenticated write-gate.\n\n## Why this blocks the flip (dc09 / pristine-horrible-whapuku)\n\nThe CI merge-gate `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml` runs `rebar verify-identity` over the\nwhole tickets store with posture/boundary from `rebar.toml`. After `require_authenticated=true`\nlands, every NEW status transition (post-enforce_since) writes an unsigned in-scope STATUS event\nthat the gate flags -> the gate FAILS -> blocks landing. So enforcement is unsafe across the\ntxn writer until this is fixed. This is a foundational signing gap the epic's 5 stories did not\nanticipate (they assumed signing worked for all writers).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `transition_core` and `claim_core` in `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py` sign their STATUS (and\n      claim EDIT) events via the same signing seam CREATE/COMMENT use (`_apply_authorship` or an\n      equivalent), so a transition/claim/close under a configured signing key produces\n      `author_sig`.\n- [ ] Under `identity.require_authenticated`, an unsignable transition of a non-exempt ticket is\n      refused by the write-gate (parity with `append_event`), while gate-exempt types\n      (session_log/code_review/identity) are unaffected.\n- [ ] A held-out regression test asserts: with a signing key configured, a transition/claim\n      STATUS event has `author_sig` and `rebar verify-identity` reports it `verified`; without a\n      key + enforcement on, the transition is refused. Proving command: `make test`.\n- [ ] No regression to txn atomicity/locking (claim writes STATUS+EDIT in one commit).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"98ae9a8a-3076-496b-902f-4ff9adef92ee","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"0ba4-6a28-7a88-47b2","ticket_type":"bug","title":"txn.py transitions/claims/closes write UNSIGNED in-scope STATUS/EDIT events (bypass the signing seam) — blocks safe require_authenticated flip","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["e1042df1-02ee-413d-88ce-fe4fc5015b30","6cd0b7fa-d1a4-4ca4-948e-f2e090755618","c737324c-14a1-4baf-9f7a-6a9569d2fc37","0c6e28a8-cb71-4c74-a4e8-207a5fcc07dd","b2928728-3ad4-4d5b-b7c6-60e53783b71e","50349147-58fa-4776-a879-cfd0c4b49f9a","08656d39-0f5d-4846-9ca3-ca6b894bc39e","98ae9a8a-3076-496b-902f-4ff9adef92ee","956eb610-7702-417b-bee2-4feeac0f1290"]},"env_id":"","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784345849269472001,"uuid":"ccf6a11c-4cb4-41c0-8217-68d9953112f4"}